    "body": "Problem: Breaking a link with update=true loses colors inherited from the linked group.\r\n\r\nSolution: Copy color indices from the linked group so inherited colors remain visible in :hi output.\r\n\r\nFix #38743 \r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38750#discussion_r3037255125"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/38750"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3037255125"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "1-line comments that explain what's going on are always worth having for these changes. It's not at all obvious what's going on here. It's really not a fun puzzle to have to figure out this kind of code everywhere. \n\n```suggestion\n      // Copy color indices from the linked group so inherited colors remain visible in :hi output.\n      HlGroup *linked = &hl_table[old_link - 1];\n```",
            "commit_id": "cf7c9335a59ce743a67d929172ab76a1f7840139",
            "created_at": "2026-04-05T19:26:00Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -965,6 +966,12 @@ void set_hl_group(int id, HlAttrs attrs, Dict(highlight) *dict, int link_id)\n       }\n     } else if (!update) {\n       *cattrs[j].dest = kColorIdxNone;\n+    } else if (old_link > 0 && cattrs[j].val >= 0) {\n+      HlGroup *linked = &hl_table[old_link - 1];",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38750#discussion_r3037255125",
